		<div id="comment_body_64192360"><p><div class="quote"><p>Can you show me the facts that better workers do not want to go to a workplace and be around other people?</p></div><p>No, because that wasn't being claimed. These are the facts being claimed:
</p><ul>
<li>The company is forcing all employees to work in the office</li><li>Some of those employees don't want to work in the office and would rather work for a company that lets them work from home</li><li>Among the employees who want to work for a company that lets them work from home, the better employees will easily find new jobs</li><li>The company that forced all employees to work in the office has now lost a number of good employees</li></ul><p>

As with any other benefit or perk, companies that offer better benefits can attract better employees.</p></div>
	</div>

